The article is a statement issued by President Trump regarding his commitment to Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs). He mentions that the funds allocated for HBCUs in the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2017, will be spent in accordance with his responsibilities under the Constitution. He reiterates his support for HBCUs and their educational missions, citing an Executive Order he signed in February to strengthen their capacity and increase opportunities for participation in federal programs. He also mentions that his Secretary of Education, Betsy DeVos, will be giving a commencement address at Bethune-Cookman University, demonstrating the administration's dedication to HBCUs. The President expresses his intention to select an Executive Director and Board for his HBCU initiative and continue working with HBCUs across the nation.